DESCRIPTION:
This file explains what this project(lab) is all about. The aim of this project is to create at least two threads that demonstrates mutual exclusion using Semaphore. This project uses the following files in order to achieve its purpose:

1. Semaphore.h: Header file for the Semaphore class.

2. Semaphore.cpp: The implementation file for the Semaphore class.

3. main.cpp: The main function file. It must create at least two threads to demonstrate mutual exclusion in action using a Semaphore.

4. Makefile: This is the project file which contains rules that tell the system how to compile the code and produce a working executable called mutualExclusion.

5. Doxyfile: This file contains the settings for the Doxygen tool. It is generated by the Doxygen program when run for the first time.

6. README: This is a text file which describes the project.



HOW TO INSTALL PROJECT:
a) To compile the code; at the terminal, type:
   make and press the enter key.
 
b) To run it, type:
   ./main and press the enter key.

c) To generate documentation, at the terminal type:
   doxygen and press the enter key.


